-- Ritz Carlton Owner Wants Shishkhanov’s Hotel, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-02-20T05:29:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-20/ritz-carlton-owner-wants-shishkhanov-s-hotel-vedomosti-says.html
The Kazakhstan-based owner of
Moscow’s Ritz Carlton hotel wants to acquire Moscow’s National
Hotel, currently owned by the family of Mikhail Shishkhanov,
president of Binbank and nephew of Russian billionaire  Mikhail Gutseriev ,  Vedomosti  said today, citing a person familiar with
the proposal.  Verny Capital Investment Co. offered $350 million for the
hotel, which is more than twice the price Shishkhanov’s family
paid at an auction in December, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story: Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow
   msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Claudia
Carpenter at   ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  